@startuml data-fetching-stack
title Data Fetching Stack — createApiFetcher

skinparam shadowing false

package "Per-upstream wrapper\n(jolpica.ts, openf1.ts, …)" {
  [fetchJolpica(path, dataClass)] as Wrapper
}

package "createApiFetcher" {
  [withRetry\n(≤3 attempts, jittered)] as Retry
  [concurrencyLimiter\n(cap = 2 per service)] as Limiter
  [fetchWithTimeout\n(AbortController, 8s)] as Timeout
}

package "Next.js" {
  [fetch.next.revalidate\n(Data Cache)] as NextCache
  [unstable_cache\n(route-level computed)] as UnstableCache
}

cloud "Upstream API" as Upstream

Wrapper --> Retry          : path, adaptiveRevalidate(dataClass)
Retry   --> Limiter        : acquire / release
Limiter --> Timeout
Timeout --> NextCache      : with next.revalidate
NextCache --> Upstream     : on miss
Upstream  --> NextCache    : 200 JSON
NextCache --> Timeout      : cached/fresh
Timeout   --> Limiter
Limiter   --> Retry
Retry     --> Wrapper

UnstableCache .down.> Wrapper : routes wrap\nexpensive computations

note right of Retry
  Retries on:
   • network error
   • HTTP 429 / 5xx
   • timeout
end note

note bottom of Limiter
  Default cap = 2.
  Lower in createApiFetcher(base, name, 1)
  for stricter upstreams.
end note

@enduml
